mni harness  virtuix vr rack  virtuix vr boom  virtuix vr stands  virtuix omni  wikipedia virtuix omni from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search virtuix omni image of virtuix omni in use in  type software inventor jan goetgeluk manufacturer virtuix website wwwvirtuixcom notes tentative release date q  subject to change virtuix omni is an omnidirectional treadmill simulator for virtual reality games and other applications it is currently in development by virtuix it uses a platform to simulate locomotion ie the motion of walking requiring both special shoes and surface that reduce friction it works in conjunction with a variety of head mounted displays such as the oculus rift htc vive gear vr and allows gamers to walk or run within the game they are playing in  the virtuix omni became one of the ten biggest technology kickstarter campaigns raising  million in funding since then virtuix has raised another  million from private and institutional investors although originally slated to be released in january  production of the omni only began in november  if the current launch target of q  is met it will have been delayed by over twoandahalfyears kickstarter backers began receiving their orders during the third week of january  contents  history  product overview  games and peripherals  military use  see also  references  external links historyedit virtuix omni design from  virtuix was founded by jan goetgeluk he quit his investment banking job to develop the project investing  months of his time and a  personal investment to develop a prototype the prototype for the omni used dummy shoes and kinect software to detect movement instead of the sensor system that became part of the final product he applied for a us patent on rd october  for his locomotion system and apparatus however there is also prior art the uks wizdish whose product is now known as rovr jan goetgeluk purchased a dish and shoes from wizdish system prior to the filing of the us patent and could have derived his work as the technology is exactly the same virtuix presented the prototype of the omni at the electronic entertainment expo  in los angeles california where it was reviewed by engadget and other electronic publications including the verge virtuix launched a kickstarter campaign in june  to raise money for manufacturing the campaign was endorsed by oculus rift founder palmer luckey and overshot its funding goal of  within three and a half hours of it being posted the campaign raised a total of  million when it closed making it one of the top  biggest technology crowdfunding campaigns at the time goetgeluk presented the virtuix omni on an episode of the tv show shark tank in  after selling approximately  units in the kickstarter campaign he failed to obtain funding from the sharks after asking for  million for  of the company however shark tank investor and billionaire mark cuban invested in virtuix after the airing of the show virtuix has raised a total of  million in additional funding from institutions and private investors investors have included  ventures seedinvest tekton ventures and scout ventures in  the company tested the waters under regulation a for a potential offering of shares to the public the omni presented at sxsw in  where virtuix founder jan goetgeluk also spoke on the topic of virtual reality the final version of the virtuix omni was presented at the  consumer electronics show in las vegas nevada it was described as sleek compared to its previous versions in january  the first production omnis began to ship to consumers by december that year virtuix announced that they would no longer be shipping kickstarter preorders to nonus customers and would not allow customers to swap their shipping address to a package forwarding service claiming the logistics and costs of shipping were unfeasible the company would refund the orders with an additional  per year from the date of the order kickstarter backers began receiving their orders during the third week of january  product overviewedit design of the virtuix omni as showcased at the  consumer electronics show in las vegas the omni is a locomotion simulator designed to work as a game controller and allow gamers to walk within the game environment in which they are playing it is used in tandem with oculus rift or other virtual reality head mounted displays and is a peripheral for a full virtual reality game setup the surface is bowl shaped and requires special low friction shoes in order to operate it it uses inertial sensors to track a persons position the length of their stride and how fast they are moving the information is then sent to a computer which translates the data into the game movements games and peripheralsedit virtuix omni acts as a standard game controller and is designed to work with any pc game virtuix is also developing travr a firstperson shooter game as well as three additional games designed specifically for the omni the virtuix omni has been reviewed in publications for games such as grand theft auto v the elder scrolls v skyrim battlefield  and arma  among others in addition to gaming the virtuix omni can be used for virtual reality applications including training and simulation fitness healthcare architecture virtual tourism meetups and events virtuix is a sponsor of hands omni a wireless glove that allows users to feel an object they are grabbing in virtual reality the glove is in development as of  and is being developed to be used as a peripheral for the omni military useedit virtuix is developing a version of the omni for use in military simulation the military version has additional forms of movement features such as accommodating a fully combatloaded soldier it was first exhibited in december  see alsoedit haptic suit cyberith virtualizer referencesedit  tweedie steven  january  how do you move in virtual reality with a treadmill like this one i just tried the business insider retrieved  may    a b c d tweed